works.description: Custom built in 2009 by Hanseatic Marine in Henderson, Australia for German eco-industrialist Guido Krass, the 73.5-metre Silver Zwei, the world’s fastest long-range superyacht. The luxury yacht has been now put on sale by the German billionaire via Burgess for €59 million (about $85 million). The yacht was designed by Espen Oeino to meet the highest standards of performance and environmental awareness. Silver Zwei is the fastest long distance cruising yacht in the world with trans-Atlantic range at 22 knots, and boasts a consumption of remarkable 360 liters per hour at 18 knots, which extends her range to 4,500nm.
